thought:
**My Analysis of the Administrative Unit Change**

Okay, I've got a query asking about the new administrative unit for the old address "Xã Xuân Hồng, Huyện Nam Đàn, Tỉnh Nghệ An."  My first step is always to verify the province's stability. Checking the "60-NQ/TW" document, "Tỉnh Nghệ An" isn't slated for any mergers, so that part's straightforward.

Now, I'm diving into the resolutions, focusing on "Xã Xuân Hồng" within Nghệ An province.  And there it is, clearly stated in "1678/NQ-UBTVQH15": item 37 explicitly mentions that "Xã Xuân Hồng" is being merged into the new ward, "xã Kim Liên."  Items 38 and 39 describe other combinations, but they don't involve "Xuân Hồng," so those are irrelevant here.

This is a strong indicator, but I always cross-reference. I'll search the other provinces. The other resolutions for "Xã Xuân Hồng" in Hà Tĩnh, Ninh Bình and Thanh Hóa. I can confidently say that these aren't the units they are looking for, because they are referring to other provinces.

So, I'm confident. The resolution in "Tỉnh Nghệ An" clearly states that "Xã Xuân Hồng" is now part of "Xã Kim Liên."  Checking the "New wards" data confirms the existence of "Xã Kim Liên" with its code and province name.
